<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <head>223. National Security Decision Memorandum 184<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d223fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials,
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Subject Files, Box
                                364, <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss>s, Nos. 145–264. Limited
                                Official Use. Copies were sent to <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SGC1">Gerard
                                    Smith</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MTH1">Moorer</persName>,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WCW1">Weinberger</persName>, and
                                David.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1972-08-14">August 14,
                                1972</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="to">
                            <item>TO <list>
                                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                                    <item>The Director, Office of Emergency Preparedness</item>
                                    <item>The Secretary of Health, Education and Welfare</item>
                                    <item>The Chairman, Atomic Energy Commission</item>
                                </list></item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <item>SUBJECT <list>
                                    <item>United States Civil Defense Policy</item>
                                </list></item>
                        </list>
                        <p>The President has reviewed the Ad Hoc Group’s response to <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 57,<note n="2" xml:id="d223fn2">See
                                    <ref target="#d222">Document 222</ref>.</note>
                            <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> civil defense policy, and the views
                            of the interested agencies.</p>
                        <p>The President has: <list>
                                <item>—Decided that the <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> shall
                                    maintain the current overall level of effort in its civil
                                    defense activities.</item>
                                <item>—Directed that there be increased emphasis on dual-use plans,
                                    procedures and preparedness within the limitations of existing
                                    authority, including appropriate related improvements in crisis
                                    management planning.</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_KHA1"><hi rend="strong">Henry A.
                                        Kissinger</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>